1.What is padding and margin and when do you use them?
padding:
Purpose: Padding is the space between the content of an element and its border.
When to use: Use padding when you want to create space inside an element, pushing the content away from the element's borders.

.example {
  padding: 10px;
}
Margin:

Purpose: Margin is the space outside the border of an element.
When to use: Use margin when you want to create space around an element, pushing it away from neighboring elements.

.example {
  margin: 10px;
}

2. What is diplay property and explain diplay inline,block,inline block?
Inline:
Description: Inline elements do not start on a new line and only take up as much width as necessary.
They flow within the content and do not create a line break after the element.
Examples: <span>, <a>, <strong>, <em>
span {
  display: inline;
}

Block:
Description: Block elements always start on a new line and take up the full width available.
They create a "block" that extends the full width of their containing element.
Examples: <div>, <p>, <h1> to <h6>
div {
  display: block;
}

Inline-Block:
Description: Inline-block elements are a combination of inline and block elements.
They do not start on a new line but can have a width and height, and they respect top and bottom margins and paddings.
Examples: <img>, <button>
img {
  display: inline-block;
}

3.Explain minheight, minwidth, maxheight, and maxwidth in CSS:
min-height:
Description: Specifies the minimum height an element can have.
Usage: Prevents an element from becoming smaller than the specified value, even if its content is smaller or if the container is smaller.
Example:
.box {
  min-height: 100px;
}
min-width:
Description: Specifies the minimum width an element can have.
Usage: Prevents an element from becoming narrower than the specified value, even if its content is narrower or if the container is narrower.
Example:
.box {
  min-width: 200px;
}

max-height:
Description: Specifies the maximum height an element can have.
Usage: Prevents an element from becoming taller than the specified value, even if its content or the container size would allow it to be taller.
Example:
.box {
  max-height: 300px;
}

max-width:
Description: Specifies the maximum width an element can have.
Usage: Prevents an element from becoming wider than the specified value, even if its content or the container size would allow it to be wider.
Example:
.box {
  max-width: 400px;
}








